commits.message: Updated vendors to their latest versions.
Stopped rworldmap default loading
removing fully qualified class name
Update 1.5 release notes for XML and formset fixes.

Merge pull request #737 from hrbonz/docs_CBV_generic_views_typo

Fixed typo in docs/topics/class-based-views/generic-display.txt
Fixes typo introduced by django/django@08dc90bccf7c4ffa8b04064d74b54c1150af5ff9. This is described in Trac ticket:19855.
Fixed #19728 - Updated API stability doc to reflect current meaning of "stable".

Merge pull request #739 from JustinTArthur/ticket-19855

Fixed typo in legacy database how to
This function is unused and should have been removed a few releases ago.
Add test for collapsible fieldset functionality in admin

Fixed #14571 -- Updated embedded jQuery from 1.4.2 to 1.9.1

Thanks dArignac for the initial patch.

Replaced the obsolete toggle event handling JS function

The toggle(func1, func2) event handling function has been removed
in jQuery 1.9.

Fixed #19598 -- Fixed jQuery tagName retrieving

Thanks rj at rudiculous.net for the report.

Added a db_constraint option to ForeignKeys.

This controls whether or not a database level cosntraint is created. This is useful in a few specialized circumstances, but in general should not be used!

Refactored negated IS NULL handling

This one cleaned up add_filter() negated filter generation. As a side
effect split_exclude() was cleaned up, too.

Refs #19849

Removed join() promote kwarg

The join promote=True was over-aggressive in select_related handling.
After that was removed, the only other user was query.combine(). That
use case is very easy to handle locally, so there is no more need for
the join(promote=True) flag.

Refs #19849.

Cleaned up join promotion in query.combine() with OR

Refs #19849

Added a test for negated Q object querying

The added test is from the patch in ticket #19672 (written by Ian
Kelly). Fixed #19672, refs #19849.
Clarified the language used in the documentation. Thanks to Mike Smith for the report.

Made a couple of selenium tests wait for page loaded

The admin_widgets tests were issuing click() to the browser but
didn't wait for the effects of those clicks. This caused the resulting
request to be processed concurrently with the test case. When using
in-memory SQLite this caused weird failures.

Also added wait_page_loaded() to admin selenium tests for code
reuse.

Fixed #19856
Fixed #19868 -- Clarified purpose of custom user example

Fixed #19870 -- Regression in select_related in inheritance cases

There was a regression in case two models inherited the same parent,
and one contained a foreign key to other. When select_related travelled
the foreign key the other model reused the parent join made by the
first model. This was likely caused by Query.join_parent_model()
addition in commit 68985db48212c701a3d975636123a5d79bdc006f.

Thanks to Trac alias loic84 for report & tests.
Factored code and added a missing docstring.

issue.title: Feature Request: Additional Character Types
issue.body:
Happy Weekend Anathema Team!

I tried searching around here to see if this was possibly discussed so I'm not duplicating a question that was already discussed.  I saw in another thread that there is work in progress to add the new features that were presented in Shards.  That's great!

My question is more in reference to the different playable character types that are not represented in this awesome program.  I'm speaking specifically of the following character types:

Alchemical Exalted
Fair Folk
Dragon Kings
Mountain Folk

Has there been any discussion about adding these character types into the mix?  If not, I would like to make a formal request.

issue.title: Invalid assertion failed in AbstractActionDesc.setLabel()
issue.body:
Hello,

I am using MouseFeed, and I managed to trigger a failure for what seems to me an invalid assertion.
It is in com.mousefeed.client.collector.AbstractActionDesc.setLabel(). Nothing prevents a label from being an empty String "". However, the SWT framework does not allow null labels.

I think the following code:
```java
    public void setLabel(final String label) {
        isTrue(isNotBlank(label));
        this.label = label.replace("&", "");
    }
```
should be rewritten like this instead:
```java
    public void setLabel(final String label) {
        isTrue(label != null);
        this.label = label.replace("&", "");
    }
```

For reference, here is the stacktrace I got:
```

!MESSAGE Unhandled event loop exception
!STACK 0
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: The validated expression is false
```

issue.title: Add view and controller path to configuration
issue.body:
Consider adding view and controller path to plugin's configuration, so projects with non-standard paths to views and / or controllers could also be handled with your plugin.

For example, my projects have views for controllers separated into extra subfolder `/protected/views/controllers/*`. This causes, that in current implementation of your plugin most functions does not work. For example `Navigation > Go to View` shows error message, that view can't be found.

This is normal, it is not a bug, because views are in non-standard folder. If you would add new field to project's configuration, where user could specify path to views, I think this would solve the problem.

There are many "barebone" examples on Yii site, that propose users to use non-standard folder organisation of their applications. It seems that any Yii project, that will use different folder structure will not be handled by a plugin in current implementation.

This is connected to #30 issue, as Yii2 folder organisation will also be different.

This is an enhancement proposition or feature request. If you don't agree with me, then close this issue without implementing these changes. Thank you for a continued support of your plugin. Great job!
